                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 8.508,
                                "byte_start": 28672,
                                "byte_stop": 62736,
                                "text": "Justice Souter has the opinion of the Court to announce in Shepard versus United States, No. 03-9168."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 8.508,
                        "stop": 336.299,
                        "byte_start": 62736,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15042,
                            "name": "David H. Souter",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/david_h_souter",
                            "last_name": "Souter",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2686,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 655362000,
                                    "date_end": 1246251600,
                                    "appointing_president": "George H. W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2686"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32703,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 42141,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/david_souter.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 6839,
                            "identifier": "david_h_souter"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 8.508,
                                "stop": 14.006,
                                "byte_start": 62736,
                                "byte_stop": 84783,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the First Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 14.006,
                                "stop": 26.739,
                                "byte_start": 84783,
                                "byte_stop": 135670,
                                "text": "The Armed Career Criminal Act provides that anyone convicted of being a felon in possession of a firearm who has three prior convictions for violent crimes must be sentenced to at least 15 years in prison."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 26.739,
                                "stop": 31.031,
                                "byte_start": 135670,
                                "byte_stop": 152806,
                                "text": "The statute defines violent crime who include burglary."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 31.031,
                                "stop": 50.738,
                                "byte_start": 152806,
                                "byte_stop": 231696,
                                "text": "In a 1990 case, Taylor against the United States, we interpreted the law\u0027s use of burglary to cover only what we then called generic burglary, by which we basically meant a burglary that involved entry into a building rather than a car or a boat or whatnot."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 50.738,
                                "stop": 62.87,
                                "byte_start": 231696,
                                "byte_stop": 280179,
                                "text": "In Taylor, the defendant\u0027s prior burglary conviction had occurred in a state with a statute providing that burglary included entries into boats and railroad cars as well as into buildings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 62.87,
                                "stop": 68.484,
                                "byte_start": 280179,
                                "byte_stop": 302644,
                                "text": "The state statute, in other words, criminalized both non-generic and generic burglary."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 68.484,
                                "stop": 84.028,
                                "byte_start": 302644,
                                "byte_stop": 364816,
                                "text": "How then was the a sentencing someone under the Armed Career Criminal Act supposed to tell whether a burglary conviction in a state like that was the generic burglary which counted under the Act or non-generic burglary which did not count?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 84.028,
                                "stop": 105.213,
                                "byte_start": 364816,
                                "byte_stop": 449557,
                                "text": "We said that a conviction under a state statute that criminalizes both generic and non-generic burglary accounts for the 15-year minimum under the Act if the charging document and the jury instructions from the earlier trial show that the jury necessarily had to find a generic burglary in order to convict the defendant."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 105.213,
                                "stop": 112.523,
                                "byte_start": 449557,
                                "byte_stop": 478814,
                                "text": "The petitioner in this case, Reginald Shepard, pleaded guilty in Federal Court to being a felon in possession of a firearm."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 112.523,
                                "stop": 122.418,
                                "byte_start": 478814,
                                "byte_stop": 518416,
                                "text": "The Government argued its sentencing that Shepard had at least three burglary convictions that counted against him under the Act and so had to receive the 15-year mandatory minimum."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 122.418,
                                "stop": 136.526,
                                "byte_start": 518416,
                                "byte_stop": 574840,
                                "text": "The District Court said no, however, noting that each of the prior burglary convictions occurred in Massachusetts, the state with a non-generic burglary statute and each followed a guilty plea rather than a trial."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 136.526,
                                "stop": 151.527,
                                "byte_start": 574840,
                                "byte_stop": 634817,
                                "text": "The charging document in each case did not limit the charge to generic burglary and because there was no trial, there were no jury instructions that showed Shepard\u0027s conviction was necessarily for generic burglary."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 151.527,
                                "stop": 163.622,
                                "byte_start": 634817,
                                "byte_stop": 683196,
                                "text": "Although the Government contended that the police reports and complaint applications from those prior convictions showed that each one involved entry into a building and thus was a generic burglary."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 163.622,
                                "stop": 169.574,
                                "byte_start": 683196,
                                "byte_stop": 707020,
                                "text": "The District Court concluded that Taylor did not permit her to examine such documents."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 169.574,
                                "stop": 176.749,
                                "byte_start": 707020,
                                "byte_stop": 735754,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals disagreed and remanded the case for a review of the police reports and complaint applications."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 176.749,
                                "stop": 189.152,
                                "byte_start": 735754,
                                "byte_stop": 785283,
                                "text": "The District Court conducted the review and again declined to impose the sentence concluding that the documents did not provide the necessary assurance that Shepard had pleaded guilty to three generic burglaries."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 189.152,
                                "stop": 195.1,
                                "byte_start": 785283,
                                "byte_stop": 809106,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals reversed again and ordered the imposition of the 15-year minimum."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 195.1,
                                "stop": 202.376,
                                "byte_start": 809106,
                                "byte_stop": 838259,
                                "text": "We granted certiorati and in an opinion filed today with the Clerk of Court, we reverse the decision of the Court of Appeals."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 202.376,
                                "stop": 219.283,
                                "byte_start": 838259,
                                "byte_stop": 905864,
                                "text": "Although Taylor involved prior burglary convictions obtained after jury trials rather than guilty pleas, the Armed Career Criminal Act gives no indication that the two types of prior convictions should be treated differently and the reasoning of Taylor itself is not limited to prior jury convictions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 219.283,
                                "stop": 228.15,
                                "byte_start": 905864,
                                "byte_stop": 941286,
                                "text": "In the context of prior jury convictions, Taylor, as mentioned, allows sentencing courts to examine the indictment and the jury instructions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 228.15,
                                "stop": 240.1,
                                "byte_start": 941286,
                                "byte_stop": 989142,
                                "text": "Taylor referred to indictments and in jury instructions for a specific reason, namely, that they can show that the jury necessarily had to find a generic burglary in order to convict."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 240.1,
                                "stop": 261.26,
                                "byte_start": 989142,
                                "byte_stop": 1073779,
                                "text": "In the context of prior of guilty pleas, we conclude that the need to show that a conviction was necessarily for generic burglary limits courts to examining, in addition to the charging documents, the written plea agreement, the transcript of the plea colloquy and any explicit factual findings by the Trial Court to which the defendant assented."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 261.26,
                                "stop": 268.997,
                                "byte_start": 1073779,
                                "byte_stop": 1104708,
                                "text": "Police reports and complaint applications cannot show that a later guilty plea was necessarily to generic burglary."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 268.997,
                                "stop": 281.681,
                                "byte_start": 1104708,
                                "byte_stop": 1155490,
                                "text": "The Government urges us to allow a more wide-ranging inquiry, but its arguments in favor of such an approach are inconsistent with Taylor and thus amount to a call to move away from that decision."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 281.681,
                                "stop": 289.177,
                                "byte_start": 1155490,
                                "byte_stop": 1185479,
                                "text": "Since Taylor was a case of statutory interpretation, the usual demands of sticking to precedent are very strong."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 289.177,
                                "stop": 302.401,
                                "byte_start": 1185479,
                                "byte_stop": 1238350,
                                "text": "We also believe that relaxing the standard as the Government asks us to do would take trial judges dangerously close to fact finding of a sort that a defendant has a constitutional right to insist that a jury make."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 302.401,
                                "stop": 315.334,
                                "byte_start": 1238350,
                                "byte_stop": 1290073,
                                "text": "Justice Thomas joins all but part three of the opinion and he has filed and opinion concurring in part and conruccing in the judgment; Justice O\u0027Connor has filed a dissenting opinion in which Justices Kennedy and Breyer join."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 315.334,
                                "stop": 336.299,
                                "byte_start": 1290073,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Chief Justice took no part in the decision of this case."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
